{{Infobox language |name= Aurá |nativename=Aurê |states=[[Brazil]] |region=[[Maranhão]] |extinct=by 2009 |familycolor=American |fam1=[[Tupian languages|Tupian]] |fam2=[[Tupi–Guarani languages|Tupi–Guaraní]] |fam3=Xingu |iso3=aux |glotto=aura1243 |glottorefname=Aura }}
'''Aurá''' is an extinct [[Tupian languages|Tupi]] language last spoken by two individuals in [[Maranhão]], [[Brazil]]. Both speakers lived with the Guajá, but originally came from [[Pará]].
