{{Infobox language |name=Gera |states=[[Nigeria]] |region=[[Bauchi State]] |speakers=200,000 |date=1995 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Afro-Asiatic |fam2=[[Chadic languages|Chadic]] |fam3=[[West Chadic languages|West Chadic]] |fam4=[[Bole–Angas languages|Bole–Angas]] |fam5=[[Bole–Tangale languages|Bole–Tangale (A.2)]] |fam6=[[Bole languages proper|Bole]] (North) |iso3=gew |glotto=gera1246 |glottorefname=Gera }}
'''Gera''' (also known as Gerawa) is an [[Afro-Asiatic languages|Afro-Asiatic]] language spoken in [[Nigeria]]. Speakers are shifting to [[Hausa language|Hausa]].<ref name=e18/>
