The '''Turks in Abkhazia''', also known as '''Abkhazian Turks''', ({{lang-tr|Abhazya Türkleri}}) are people of [[Turkish people|Turkish]] ancestry  who have had a thriving presence in [[Abkhazia]] since the rule of the [[Ottoman Empire]].<ref name=TodaysZaman>{{cite web|author=Today's Zaman|title=Abkhazian President Bagapsh in Ankara|url=http://www.todayszaman.com/columnist-240558-abkhazian-president-bagapsh-in-ankara.html|accessdate=2012-03-06|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110410205847/http://www.todayszaman.com/columnist-240558-abkhazian-president-bagapsh-in-ankara.html|archivedate=2011-04-10|df=}}</ref> Today, the community numbers about 10,000-15,000.<ref name=DG/><ref name=BulTurk/>

